description:
Uh oh!  
Dash found a hideous creature near Castle Creepenstein!

puzzles.description: Make Dash automatically turn on red lights, show a pattern in the eye ring, play the growl sound, and move forward.
puzzles.introduction: This ogre looks like a nasty piece of work.

puzzles.description: After moving forward, make Dash automatically turn on red lights again.
puzzles.introduction: The ogre will keeping coming at you if you create a loop.

hints.description: Make a loop! Link the Move Forward state to the Red light using an Auto cue.

puzzles.description: Make Dash use the listener to do nothing when an obstacle is seen close behind Dash.
puzzles.introduction: The ogre has a weak spot on its back. Just poke it there to defeat it.

hints.description: Drag out a Listener state and a Do Nothing state. Link the states with an Obstacle Seen cue. Make sure the cue is set to only detect obstacles that are very close behind Dash.

puzzles.description: After doing nothing, make Dash wait for 2.0 s then say "Help!".
puzzles.introduction: The ogre doesn't sound so tough now!

hints.description: Link the "Help!" sound to the Do Nothing state using a Wait For cue set to 2.0 s.

puzzles.description: Make Dash turn off an eye light every 1.0 s.  Make Dash finish with all of the eye lights turned off.
puzzles.introduction: Looks like the ogre is shutting down.

hints.description: Link the Eye Ring states together using Wait For cues set to 1.0 s.

puzzles.description: After turning off the eye lights, make Dash automatically go to sleep. Then make Dash automatically turn the lights off and automatically turn off the eye lights again.
puzzles.introduction: When you defeat the ogre, it falls asleep.
